MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/game-server/src/(d1-persistence|machine-actions)\.ts$
ADVISORY: |
  `isJournalable` in d1-persistence.ts gates more than D1 persistence ‚Äî it is the
  upstream guard in machine-actions.ts `persistFactToD1` that also controls whether
  `factToTicker` and `handleFactPush` run for the fact.

  Practical consequence: a fact type missing from JOURNALABLE_TYPES has its ticker
  message silently dropped AND its push notification silently dropped. Discovered
  2026-04-14 while debugging why Pulse narrator lines ("Luna Star started talking
  to someone") were not rendering for first-DM creation ‚Äî DM_INVITE_SENT was not
  in the list.

  Rules:
    - If a new fact type needs to drive a ticker message (factToTicker returns a
      TickerMessage for it) OR a push notification (handleFactPush cases on it),
      it MUST be added to JOURNALABLE_TYPES.
    - Do not remove DM_INVITE_SENT from JOURNALABLE_TYPES without also refactoring
      persistFactToD1 so ticker/push don't share the same early return.

  Long-term fix (not yet applied): split the gate ‚Äî D1 persistence uses
  `isJournalable`, ticker and push each get their own guards so semantics are
  independent. If you're doing that refactor, remove this guardrail.
